This paper deals with community detection in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the analysis of social networks. The second likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as community detection algorithms are often implemented as software tools. The third likely sub-category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), which deals with the application of computational methods to social science research. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as community detection algorithms are based on graph theory and require efficient data structures and algorithms. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as community detection can be seen as a form of clustering, which is a common task in machine learning and AI.
